  "parent": "pt-BR",
  "notes": "Mineiro (Minas Gerais, Belo Horizonte-centred). Diagnostic: strong pretonic mid-vowel raising /e/ -> [i], /o/ -> [u] (menino -> [miЛҲninu], coruja -> [kuЛҲЙҫuК’Йҗ]) by vowel harmony and consonant-driven reduction (Lemos & Viegas 2016:314-315; Viegas 1987), modelled in the pre-lexical positional map (grapheme e/o). Coda /S/ stays alveolar [s,z] - NOT the Carioca chiado - inherited unchanged from the pt-BR base, so no coda-sibilant allophone rule is declared. Full /t,d/ palatalisation. Transitional rhotic: BH city uses the tap [Йҫ], the rural interior shares the caipira retroflex [Й»] (noted, not the encoded default). Extreme posttonic reduction and syllable loss are stereotyped but prosodic, not encoded.",
  "quality": "research",
  "script_type": "alphabet",
