      "pages": "314-333",
      "notes": "p.314-315: in Minas Gerais dialects the pretonic mid vowels /e o/ raise to [i u] (p[i]rigo 'perigo', c[u]mida 'comida', m[i]nino 'menino', b[u]neca 'boneca'), by vowel harmony with a following high vowel and by consonant-driven vowel reduction; Viegas (1987) established the role of the lexical item. Grounds the pretonic-raising positional rules of this spec."
